Personally, I say if a statement continues on a different line, then you should use braces<p><pre><code>    //okay
    if (condition) return foo;

    //not okay
    if (condition)
        return foo;

    //not okay
    if (condition) do_foo();
    else do_bar();
</code></pre>
In the second case, the else can be considered a continuation.  In the first example, there&#x27;s little chance of confusion or the introduction of an error, in the second and third, that is not necessarily the case.<p>If it doesn&#x27;t look/fit well on one line, break it up with braces.
